- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the implications of using personal health data shared on social media. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper discusses the use of a sleep-tracking mobile application. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possibility as the paper discusses the value of combining social media data with sleep data. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze sleep logs on Twitter.
